comment: Lopez (BKN) and Nowitzki (DAL) briefly engage and then separate.
As he backs down in the post, Lopez (BKN) tangles up Nowitzki's (DAL) arms affecting his ability to defend.
Nowitzki (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position and Parsons (DAL) makes incidental contact with Lopez's (BKN) non-shooting arm that does not affect his shot attempt.
Lopez (BKN) affects Nowitzki's (DAL) FOM away from the ball as he attempts to set a screen.
Young (BKN) and Nowitzki (DAL) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Lopez (BKN) jumps from point A to point B and makes body-to-body contact with Barea (DAL) that affects his driving shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Young (BKN) was behind the three-point line on his made field goal was upheld.
Young (BKN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Barea's (DAL) drive and shot attempt.
Parsons (DAL) and Lopez (BKN) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
LHH shows Young (BKN) cleanly strips the ball from Parsons (DAL), who then regains possession.
Young (BKN) and Nowitzki (DAL) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Barea (DAL) sets the hand-off screen on Jack (BKN), giving him room to avoid the contact.
Lopez (BKN) legally contests Matthews' (DAL) driving layup attempt.
Nowitzki (DAL) sets a screen on Larkin (BKN), who is stationary, and therefore he does not need to give him room to avoid the screen. Nowitzki absorbs contact when it occurs.
Lopez (BKN) firms up as he sets the screen on Barea (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LATR shows Jack (BKN) makes incidental contact with Barea (DAL) as he drives to the basket. Barea is in a legal guarding position.
Parsons (DAL) makes incidental contact with Young (BKN) as they attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Young (BKN) obtains a legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Barea (DAL).
Barea (DAL) dives over the back of Young (BKN), making incidental contact as he attempts to secure the loose ball.
Lopez (BKN) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) establishes a legal screening position on Larkin (BKN).
Parsons' (DAL) foot contact with the ball is not intentional and therefore not a violation.
Johnson (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Nowitzki's (DAL) post move and layup attempt.
Lopez (BKN) maintains a legal screening position on Matthews (DAL), giving him room to avoid the contact.
Pachulia (DAL) grabs and holds Lopez's (BKN) arm and affect his FOM away from the ball.
Parsons (DAL) makes incidental contact with Lopez (BKN) on his off-ball cut.
Matthews (DAL) legally contests Jack's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
